{"title_page": "Solo Leveling", "text_new": "{{Use mdy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{italic title|noerror|string=Solo Leveling|all=yes}}\n{{Infobox manhwa\n| name         = Solo Leveling\n| image        = Solo Leveling Webtoon.png\n| hangul       = \ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5\n| romanized    = Na Honjaman Level-up\n| genre        = Action, Fantasy\n| Adaptation   = \n| author       = Chu-Gong\n| illustrator  = Jang Sung-Rak\n| publisher    = D&C Media<!--The publisher for webtoon in print is D&C Media (\ub514\uc564\uc528\ubbf8\ub514\uc5b4). DO NOT use Kakao as the publisher.-->\n| magazine     = {{ubl|[[KakaoPage]] (South Korea)|[[Piccoma]] (Japan)}}\n| first        = 2018\n| firstmo      = March 4,\n| last         = 2020\n| lastmo       = March 19,\n| volumes      = 2\n| chapter_list = #Volume list\n| related      = \n}}\n'''''Solo Leveling''''' ({{Korean|hangul=\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5|rr=Na Honjaman Level-up|lit=I Alone Level Up|labels=yes}}) is a South [[Korean language|Korean]] novel written by Chu-Gong. It was serialized in Papyrus and later in [[Kakao]]'s media platform [[KakaoPage]] and concluded with 14 volumes and 270 chapters. The novel has been licensed in English by Webnovel under the title '''''Only I Level Up'''''.\n\nThe webtoon adaptation has been serialized in KakaoPage since March 4, 2018, illustrated by Jang Sung-Rak. Its first season concluded on March 19, 2019. The individual chapters collected and published by D&C Media into two volumes as of April 2020. ''Solo Leveling'' has been translated to many languages by way of [[fan translations]].\n\n== Plot ==\nSince a portal connecting our world to a world full of monsters and creatures of all kinds appeared, some people have acquired powers and the ability to hunt them: they are called hunters. The protagonist of the story, Sung Jin-Woo, is the weakest of the rank E hunters and barely stronger than a normal human. He is nicknamed by his fellow hunters as \"the weakest\". One day, he and other hunters find themselves trapped in an extremely dangerous dungeon, and only a few of them survive and manage to escape. Sung Jin-Woo himself hardly survives and is the only one who completes all the trials in this dungeon. He then turns into a \"player\" who can now see an interface showing him quests. Will he succeed in becoming the most powerful hunter?\n\nThe manhwa depicts how the weakest of all the hunters grows to become the strongest there is. Hunter Sung-Woo likes clearing dungeons alone and have gained tremendous strength and magic powers in the process. The Ant arc just finished and Sung Jin-Woo was able to defeat the Ant king without even using his full strength. The main antagonist of the manhwa seems to be a demon who is working from the shadows and we expect him to be the last and final boss in the journey of hunter Sung Jin-Woo leveling up.\n\n== Media ==\n===Novel===\n{{Infobox novel\n|name       = Solo Leveling\n|author     = Chu-Gong\n|language   = Korean\n|country    = South Korea\n|genre      = Action, Fantasy\n|published  = {{ubl|Papyrus|[[KakaoPage]]|Webnovel (English)}}\n|pub_date   = {{ubl|February 14, 2014 (Papyrus)|February 17, 2017 \u2013 October 10, 2018 (KakaoPage)|December 21, 2018 \u2013 June 24, 2019 (Webnovel)}}\n|media_type = Novel\n|isbn       = 1170336663\n}}\n''Solo Leveling'' is written by Chu-gong. It was serialized in Papyrus and later in [[Kakao]]'s media platform [[KakaoPage]] and concluded with 14 volumes and 270 chapters.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.ipapyrus.co.kr/?document_srl=2545847|script-title=ko: :::\uafc8\uacfc \ud76c\ub9dd\uc774 \uc0b4\uc544\uc788\ub294 \ud30c\ud53c\ub8e8\uc2a4::: - \ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5|website=Papyrus|access-date=August 5, 2019|title=Archived copy|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20161224123522/http://www.ipapyrus.co.kr/?document_srl=2545847|archive-date=December 24, 2016|url-status=live}}</ref> Since 2016, the novel has garnered 1.4 million readers.<ref>{{cite web|last=Eun-ju|first=Je|url=http://www.kookje.co.kr/news2011/asp/newsbody.asp?code=0500&key=20191225.99099011853|script-title=ko:\uc81c\ubaa9\ucc98\ub7fc \ud63c\uc790 \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5\ud558\ub294 '\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5'...\"'\uc6d0\ud53c\uc2a4' \uc81c\uce58\uace0 1\uc704\"|website=Kookje Shinmun|language=ko|date=December 25, 2019|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref> The novel has been licensed in English by Webnovel under the title ''Only I level up'' since December 21, 2018 to June 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.webnovel.com/book/12507348206677105/Only-I-level-up|title=Only I level up (Solo Leveling)|website=Webnovel|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n\n===Manhwa===\n''Solo Leveling'' was launched in Kakao's webtoon platform [[KakaoPage]] on March 4, 2010 and concluded its first season on March 19, 2020.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://page.kakao.com/home?seriesId=50866481|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 [\ub3c5\uc810\uc5f0\uc7ac]|website=KakaoPage|language=ko|access-date=August 5, 2019|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190708130756/https://page.kakao.com/home?seriesId=50866481|archive-date=July 8, 2019|url-status=live}}</ref> Its first [[trade paperback (comics)|collected volume]] was released by D&C Media on September 26, 2019.\n\nIn Japan, ''Solo Leveling'' was launched in [[Kakao Japan]]'s service [[Piccoma]], and has over 1 million cumulative readership.<ref>{{cite web|last=Ho-cheol|first=Seong|url=https://news.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2020/04/19/2020041900272.html|script-title=ko:\uc77c\ubcf8 \uc0ac\ub85c\uc7a1\ub2e4, \uc6f9\ud230 '\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5' 100\ub9cc \ub3c5\uc790 \ub3cc\ud30c|website=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|language=ko|date=April 19, 2020|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref> It was also selected as #1 webtoon in Piccoma's \"Best of 2019\"<ref>{{cite web|last=Soo-yoon|first=Kang|url=https://newsis.com/view/?id=NISX20200110_0000885164|script-title=ko:\ub514\uc564\uc528\ubbf8\ub514\uc5b4 '\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5' \u65e5\uc11c \uc62c\ud574\uc758 \uc6f9\ud230 \uc120\uc815|website=[[Newsis]]|language=ko|date=January 10, 2020|access-date=April 23, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200423134302/https://newsis.com/view/?id=NISX20200110_0000885164|archive-date=April 23, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Woo-ri|first=No|url=http://www.etoday.co.kr/news/view/1843662|script-title=ko:\ub514\uc564\uc528\ubbf8\ub514\uc5b4, \u2019\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5\u2019, \u65e5 \ud53d\ucf54\ub9c8 2019 \uc6f9\ud230 1\uc704|website=EToday|language=ko|date=January 10, 2020|access-date=April 23, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200110034427/http://www.etoday.co.kr/news/view/1843662|archive-date=January 10, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|last=Jong-oh|first=Park|url=https://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=01656406625637392|script-title=ko:\uc6f9\ud230 \u2018\ub098\ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5\u2019 \uc5f4\ud48d\uc5d0 \ub514\uc564\uc528\ubbf8\ub514\uc5b4 \ubaa9\ud45c\uac00\u2191-NH|website=EDaily|language=ko|date=January 13, 2020|access-date=April 23, 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20200423133452/https://www.edaily.co.kr/news/read?newsId=01656406625637392|archive-date=April 23, 2020|url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n====Volume list====\n{{Graphic novel list/header\n| OneLanguage     = yes\n| Language        = Korean\n| Width           = 75%\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 01\n| RelDate         = September 26, 2019<ref name=\"vol1\">{{cite web|url=https://book.naver.com/bookdb/book_detail.nhn?bid=15407921|script-title=ko:\ub098 \ud63c\uc790\ub9cc \ub808\ubca8\uc5c5 1|website=[[Naver|Naver Book Database]]|language=ko|access-date=April 23, 2020}}</ref>\n| ISBN            = 979-1-18-932029-4\n| LicensedRelDate =\n| LicensedISBN    =\n| ChapterList     =\n}}\n{{Graphic novel list\n| VolumeNumber    = 02\n