ate=16 April 2020}}</ref> and lost in the second qualifying round of the [[1998\u201399 UEFA Cup|UEFA Cup]] to [[SK Sigma Olomouc|Sigma Olomouc]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://www.worldfootball.net/report/europa-league-qual-1998-1999-2-runde-kilmarnock-fc-sigma-olomouc/ | title=Kilmarnock 0 2 Sigma Olomouc | publisher=worldfootball.net | accessdate=16 April 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Results and fixtures==\n\n''Kilmarnock's score comes first''\n\n{{legend2|#CCFFCC|Win|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFFFCC|Draw|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#FFCCCC|Loss|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n{{legend2|#CCCCCC|Postponed|border=1px solid #AAAAAA}}\n\n===Scottish Premier League===\n{{Main article|1998\u201399 Scottish Premier League}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"font-size:100%; text-align:center\"\n!Match!!Date!!Opponent!!Venue!!Result!!Attendance!!Scorers\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|1||1 August 1998||[[Dundee United F.C.|Dundee United]]||H||2\u20130||8,208||[[Paul Wright (footballer)|Wright]] 32', [[Pat Nevin|Nevin]] 72'\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|2||15 August 1998||[[St Johnstone F.C.|St Johnstone]]||A||0\u20130||6,210||\n|-style=\"background: #FFCCCC;\"\n|3||22 August 1998||[[Rangers F.C.|Rangers]]||H||1\u20133||17,608||[[Paul Wright (footballer)|Wright]] 52'\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|4||30 August 1998||[[Heart of Midlothian F.C.|Heart of Midlothian]]||H||3\u20130||10,376||[[Ally McCoist|McCoist]] 8', 61', 86'\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|5||12 September 1998||[[Celtic F.C.|Celtic]]||A||1\u20131||58,361||[[J\u00e9r\u00f4me Vareille|Vareille]] 50'\n|-style=\"background: #FFFFCC;\"\n|6||19 September 1998||[[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]||A||0\u20130||6,821||\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|7||23 September 1998||[[Dundee F.C.|Dundee]]||H||2\u20131||7,069||[[Ally McCoist|McCoist]] 21', [[Kevin McGowne|McGowne]] 89'\n|-style=\"background: #CCFFCC;\"\n|8||27 September 1998||[[Aberdeen F.C.|Aberdeen]]||A||1\u20130||13,048||[[Paul Wrigh